  "title": "Simple circuits - is Bulb 3 lit with switch open",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular circuit diagram with a battery, three light bulbs, and open switch. The circuit has four horizontal branches and two vertical branches. The top horizontal branch has the battery. The bottom horizontal branch has a light bulb labeled Bulb 3. The inner horizontal branch immediately below the top horizontal branch has a light bulb labeled Bulb 2. The inner horizontal branch immediately above the bottom horizontal branch has the open switch. The left vertical branch has a light bulb labeled Bulb 1 between the two inner horizontal branches.\" src=\"/images/24262c8c77ae4281ad0df596190616e7.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A battery, three light bulbs, and a switch are connected in a circuit as shown in the figure. With the switch in the open position, which of the following correctly states if there is a current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> and provides a correct justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is a current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because charge from the battery is repelled and moves as far from the battery as possible, through Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is a current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> is part of a closed circuit loop that includes a battery.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is no current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because charge from the battery will reach the open switch first and will not be able to continue moving to Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is no current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because the switch results in an open circuit, preventing current occurring anywhere in the circuit.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
